HEADWATERS WIND FARM II LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Headwaters Wind Farm II ("Headwaters II") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Headwaters II generating facility ("Headwaters II Facility").
The Headwaters II Facility is a wind turbine generating facility located in Randolph County, Indiana. The Headwaters II Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by AEP Indiana Michigan Power Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Headwaters II's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Headwaters II Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Headwaters II's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Headwaters II shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $826,646.10. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $68,887.18.
